                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.01/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">American Legion</hi>”</placeName>,
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-27T12:00:00">November 27,
                            1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. For the Acting Secretary and Caffery. Please telegraph me at Montevideo the
                    controlling facts and conditions to date against recognition of the Grau San
                    Martín regime in Cuba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
